</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[189,1399,1001,1133]" pageId="31" pageNumber="78">
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,450,1001,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonidi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,450,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="78">Amblypsilopus leonidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[458,549,1001,1027]" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[681,866,1001,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andasibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[681,866,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="78">A. andasibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[873,964,1001,1027]" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[1020,1118,1001,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1020,1118,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="78">A. olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1126,1216,1001,1027]" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in habitus. The last two species differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[520,634,1036,1062]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonidi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[520,634,1036,1062]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="78">A. leonidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[642,733,1036,1062]" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the fore tarsomeres 4–5 white or tarsomere 5 entirely white, and the male cercus with a strongly projected median lobe. The fore tarsomeres 4–5 are entirely black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[289,403,1106,1133]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="leonidi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[289,403,1106,1133]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="78">A. leonidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[411,505,1107,1133]" pageId="31" pageNumber="78" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; the cercus has median and ventral lobes subequal in length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
